Where are you?
你在哪里？

11
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,760
Munir!
尼穆尔?

12
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,240
Where are you, sir?
你在哪？

13
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,200
Munir?
尼穆尔?

14
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:05,080
Have you gone to a vacation or something?
你去度假了吗？

15
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,640
No.
没有

16
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,420
So Munir has never been alone? 
尼穆尔从来没有一个人在家待过吗？

17
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:11,150
No.
没有

18
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,680
You haven't delayed his treatment?
你从来没有延误它的治疗？

19
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:19,160
No, I was giving him the cat food that you gave me for his...
没有，我给它的食物是您给我用于治疗它的......

20
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,560
Acute kidney failure. 
急性肾功能衰竭

21
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:22,050
Yes.
是

22
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,040
Did he die because of that?
他是因此而死吗？

23
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:27,880
Because of acute kidney failure.
因为急性肾衰竭

24
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:31,640
Not just that. The cat has also been dehydrated.
不仅如此，它也已经脱水了

25
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:33,680
How?
什么？

26
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:03,040
MUNIR - MY LOVELY CAT
尼穆尔 - 我可爱的猫

27
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,600
Man, what are we going to do with her?
兄弟，我们该拿她怎么办？

28
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:44,820
She's been here for six months.
她来这里已经六个月了

29
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:46,560
and they are still talking about Nevra.
但人们仍然在谈论内芙拉

30
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,600
You are bothered because you couldn't sleep with her.
你是因为睡不到她才觉得难受吧

31
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:54,760
Fuck off. What the fuck are you talking about?
滚蛋，你他妈在说什么？

32
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,070
How many of my classmates is crazy about coming here
我有很多同学想来这里都想疯了

33
00:11:57,070 --> 00:11:58,070
do you know?
你知道吗？

34
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:08,360
She literally came here out of nowhere.
她简直就是凭空出现的

35
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,600
Do you know why? Because she is a woman.
你知道为什么吗？因为她是女人

36
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,760
They called it positive discrimination.
他们称其为积极性区别对待

37
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,350
What part of this is positive? 
哪里有积极的一面？

38
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:15,950
There are many strong men out there.
外面有好多猛男呢

39
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:21,920
But for them it's necessary to put Nevra into the spotlight.
但对他们来说，有必要将内芙拉放在首位

40
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,240
Nevra, Nevra.
内芙拉, 内芙拉.

41
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:29,200
Fuck that thing called 'human resources'.
去他妈的“人力资源部”

42
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:43,050
What does it have to do with that?
这和这有什么关系？

43
00:12:43,050 --> 00:12:45,050
Let's say you're out there with Nevra.
假设您和内芙拉在一起

44
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:50,480
Would you trust Nevra? Could you trust her?
你会信任内芙拉吗？你会信任她吗？

45
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:57,040
I would trust more if it was a man holding the gun.
如果是个拿枪的男人，我会相信的

46
00:12:57,760 --> 00:13:00,120
At least it would be clear what he'd do.
至少很清楚他会做什么

47
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,220
See
是啊

48
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,960
She can get the fuck out of here.
她应该滚出这个地方了

49
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:11,600
But she shouldn't go without a fuck.
但是绝不能让她轻易离开

50
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:17,120
Definitely.
必须的

51
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:21,800
Nurten, could you schedule an appointment for next week, please?
奴尔滕，你能安排下星期的预约吗？

52
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,240
Agah Beyoglu.
阿加 贝尤鲁.

53
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:25,880
Thanks.
谢谢

54
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:27,840
Now...
好了

55
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:31,520
First thing we should do is to inform your family.
首先我们应该通知您的家人

56
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,040
They have to know about this first.
他们必须先知道这件事

57
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,120
Your wife had passed away.
你老婆去世了

58
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,080
Yes.
是

59
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,480
It's been 10 years.
已经十年了

60
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:42,800
You have a daughter.
你有一个女儿

61
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:45,960
Yes, but she's not here, she's living abroad.
是的，但是她不在这里，她住在国外

62
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:48,480
Doesn't matter, you should inform her.
没关系，你应该通知她

63
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:50,840
She may even call me, I would like to talk to her.
她甚至可以打电话给我，我想和她聊一下

64
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:52,560
Are we clear?
清楚吗？

65
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:55,760
Yes.
是

66
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,480
Bon appetit.
祝你好胃口

67
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:34,440
I was thinking if we should redo the test, in case the results are wrong.
我在想是否应该重做检测，以防结果不准确

68
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,560
I knew a guy named Necmi.
我认识一个叫内奇米的人

69
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:39,320
- They said he had cancer but then... - I know.
-他们说他得了癌症，但是后来......-我知道

70
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,400
I know.
我知道

71
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,000
It's hard to accept.
很难接受

72
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:45,560
But the results are clear.
但是结果很清楚

73
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,040
So are the symptoms.
症状也是如此

74
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:51,720
For me, there is no doubt in this diagnosis, Agah.
诊断毫无疑问，阿加

75
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,240
You have early stage Alzheimer's.
你有早期的老年痴呆症

76
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,120
Yes, Dad?
爸爸

77
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,880
Honey.
宝贝

78
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:08,320
Dad, I can't do it. I can't bear this anymore.
爸爸，我做不下去，我再也受不了了。

79
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,880
What happened? I'll call the Chief Inspector
怎么了？我打电话给总检察长

80
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:15,680
Dad, I'm not a kid. I don't want you to call anyone.
爸爸，我不是孩子了，我不需要你打电话给任何人

81
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,120
Then why did you call me?
那你为什么给我打电话

82
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,560
Daughter?
闺女？

83
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,520
Dau...
闺......

84
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,520
But doctor, I remember everything.
但是医生，我记得所有事情

85
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:39,080
People forget things when they have Alzheimer's.
人们患老年痴呆症时会忘记事情

86
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:41,600
I worked at the courthouse for 27 years.
我在法院工作了27年

87
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:44,720
If I went there now I'd remember where every file is.
如果我现在过去，我记得所有文件的位置

88
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,360
You are in the early stages.
你还处于初期

89
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:51,080
Ask me then, anything. My anniversary, friends' phone numbers...
随便问我生日，朋友的电话号码等等……

90
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:52,440
I know them by heart.
这些我都记得很熟

91
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:55,240
My friends used to call me I was like a phone book.
我的朋友曾经说我就像电话簿

92
00:15:55,960 --> 00:16:00,480
Back then we couldn't save the numbers so I memorized them.
当年我们无法保存电话号码，所以我就记在脑子里

93
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,080
Agah.
阿加

94
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:05,680
You forgot to give water to your cat.
你忘记给猫喝水了

95
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,080
You forgot to feed him.
你忘了给它喂食

96
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,160
He starved to death.
它饿死了

97
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,760
How could I do that? How?
我怎么会这样？怎么回事？

98
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:19,040
Poor Munir.
可怜的尼穆尔

99
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:33,000
Look, this is an early diagnosis.
听好，这是早期诊断

100
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:36,120
This will be of tremendous help for the treatment.
对治疗有极大的帮助

101
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:40,440
We have patients that lived 20 years after the diagnosis.
我们有一些患者在确诊后已经生活了20年

102
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:42,920
So rest assured.
所以请放心

103
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:46,840
Lived 20 years but do they remember what they lived?
活了20年，但他们还记得自己的生活吗？

104
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:50,680
Alzheimer's directly affects memory.
老年痴呆症直接影响记忆

105
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:54,520
It's one of the main reasons for dementia.
这是痴呆症的主要原因之一

106
00:16:55,160 --> 00:17:00,240
But we will do all we can to stall this and to keep your mind alive.
但是，我们将竭尽所能保持您的头脑活跃

107
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:03,320
But sooner or later, I will forget things, right?
但是迟早我会忘记的，对吗？

108
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:05,200
Don't think about this now.
现在先不要考虑这些

109
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:11,480
All my memories, experiences will be erased, they will go away.
我所有的记忆，经历将被抹去，并且消失

110
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:15,240
What will happen to me?
然后我会怎样？

111
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,600
I mean...
我是说……

112
00:17:18,320 --> 00:17:20,200
Phone numbers aren't that important.
电话号码没有多重要

113
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,880
But what will happen to my personality?
但是我的人格将会怎样？

114
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,480
Wouldn't it be erased too?
也会被抹掉吗？

115
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,320
I will forget what kind of man I am.
我会忘记我是什么样的人

116
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:35,640
You are alive but you don't exist.
你还活着，但你并不存在

117
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:41,040
How can someone endure this?
怎么会有人忍受得了呢？

118
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,440
You may put this in your pocket.
您可以把它放在口袋里

119
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:01,760
I'll check the sound, say something, please.
我来检查一下声音，请说点什么。

120
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:03,520
What should I say? Hi. 
我应该说什么？

121
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,800
You can count the days of the week.
您可以数一数每周有多少天

122
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:09,240
Friday, Saturday, Sunday.
星期五，星期六，星期天

123
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:10,400
Monday.
星期一

124
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,720
Tuesday, Wednesday.
星期二，星期三

125
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,280
Thursday, Friday.
星期四，星期五

126
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:16,960
That should do.
可以了

127
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:19,840
Let's get started.
让我们开始吧

128
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:42,120
I'll start with a basic question.
我从一个基本问题开始

129
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:45,600
How does it feel to be the only woman
作为唯一的女人感觉如何

130
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:48,320
working in an homicide bureau with 140 staff members?
在拥有140名员工的凶杀科工作？

131
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:51,880
How does it feel?
感觉怎么样？

132
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,160
Of course it's amazing.
当然很棒

133
00:18:57,680 --> 00:19:00,280
I feel very privileged.
我感到非常荣幸

134
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:07,120
First of all, all of us here are part of the homicide bureau.
首先，我们所有人都是凶杀科的成员

135
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:10,840
It's impossible to see anything like gender discrimination
这里几乎没有任何性别歧视

136
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:15,560
or any other sexist approaches in this institution.
或的其他任何性别歧视的方式

137
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:24,800
Instead of any problems, my friends are supporting me so much.
没有任何问题，我的朋友们都很支持我

138
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,200
Which also means another responsibility for me.
对我来说也是一种责任

139
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:32,600
I am trying to do my best to be worthy of their support.
我正在尽我所能来得到他们的支持

140
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:07,580
You studied public administration, right? 
您学习过公共管理，对吗？

141
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:08,280
Yes.
是

142
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:11,200
You even worked as a manager in private sector
您甚至在私营企业做过经理

143
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:13,560
but then you decided to enroll at the police academy.
但后来您决定报名参加警察学院

144
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:14,520
Yes.
是

145
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,880
Why did you decide to become a police officer?
您为什么决定当警察？

146
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:21,000
I always thought about it because...
我一直都想做，因为……

147
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:25,920
The greatest man I know was a policeman... My father.
我的父亲是一名警察，他是我认识的最伟大的人

148
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:28,640
Who is currently retired.
现在退休了

149
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,840
You start to understand things as you grow.
随着成长，我开始理解一些事情

150
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:36,520
We barely saw our father.
我们几乎看不到我们父亲

151
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:38,960
Maybe at the weekends, just for a day.
也许周末可以，但只有一天

152
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:41,360
I used to resent him.
我曾经很讨厌他

153
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:44,160
I used to tell him that he cares about other people more.
我曾经说他更关心别人

154
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:49,400
It seems that my father's job is to care about other people.
看来我父亲的工作就是关心别人

155
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:52,040
And he ingrained this concept in me so much
他把这个概念深深地印在我的脑海里

156
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:55,840
that I don't know how to live any other way.
以至于我不知道如何以其他方式生活

157
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,680
I actually repeat this in every interview
我在每次访谈时都会重复这句话

158
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:04,720
but being a police officer is not a job for me, never has been.
但是当警察对我来说从来就不是一份工作

159
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:10,320
There is a concept called goodness.
有一个概念叫做善良

160
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:15,000
For me, being a police officer means being a part of that goodness.
对我来说，成为一名警察意味着成为善良的一部分

161
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,320
That's my purpose...
那就是我的目标

162
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:19,760
To become a good person...
成为一个好人

163
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:41,320
Deva!
德瓦!

164
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:45,240
Deva, answer me! Where were you last night?
德瓦，回答我！昨晚你在哪里？

165
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,880
Deva, answer me!
德瓦，回答我！

166
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,800
Yes? 
喂？

167
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,470
Zuhal, hello my dear.
Zuhal，你好亲爱的

168
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:58,560
Wait a minute.
等一下

169
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,880
Tell me where were you last night.
告诉我昨晚你在哪里

170
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:05,400
Look at me!
看着我！

171
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:08,080
Where are you going?
你要去哪里？

172
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,040
Come with me then.
那你跟我来啊

173
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,800
You're not going!
你不可以去！

174
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,240
Deva, I'll fuck you up!
德瓦，我要揍死你!

175
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:16,760
Deva!
德瓦!

176
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:23,800
Yes?
喂？

177
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:28,080
My dear, is this a bad time? Did I wake you up? What time is it there?
亲爱的，这个时间不方便吗？我吵醒你了吗？现在几点了？

178
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:31,840
No, we are awake. It's morning here. Is something wrong?
不，我们都醒着，这边是早上，出什么事情了？

179
00:22:32,840 --> 00:22:35,960
Do I need a reason to call my daughter?
我给我的女儿打电话还需要理由吗？

180
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:40,320
I don't remember the last time you called.
我都不记得你上一次来电话了

181
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,000
I'm the one who always calls.
一直都是我给你打电话

182
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:46,120
How is Deva? 
德瓦怎么样？

183
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,470
Deva is making me crazy!
德瓦快把我逼疯了

184
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,240
Deva doesn't listen to me, we can't even talk...
